		<div class="comment-body"><p>Excellent points Jack.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m not 100% sure, but even though they are unlikely to be defaulted they can be called if I remember right.</p>
<p>You are correct on the Zero %, that&#8217;s why you have to watch them like a hawk.<br />
Even with a rate of 0%, with the inflation rate right now they still pay almost 5X what most CD&#8217;s do. For now&#8230;.</p>
<p>Due to the liquidity limitations they should only be used to diversify long term monies and are an advanced investment vehicle.<br />
That&#8217;s why I have less than 3% of my assets there <img src="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" class="wp-smiley" /> </p>
