													</span><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>I would try to do both depending on the debt load/class but honestly the right way is </p>
<p>1.  Save at least 1K and 2K is better while paying the minimum<br />
2.  Now put every extra penny you can on the smallest debt<br />
3.  When the smallest debt is repaid take all the money you were paying on it and roll it up to the next debt in line<br />
4.   Wash rinse repeat until all debt is gone</p>
</div>

