		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>Roundabouts,</p>
<p>First, great job on being able to save over 1/2 your income even with ongoing issues (aren&#8217;t those &#8220;issues&#8221; called &#8220;life&#8221;?).  That&#8217;s quite an achievement!</p>
<p>You said, &#8220;It can be very surprising how many small leaks you can find when you look close.&#8221;  Truer words were rarely spoken.  It&#8217;s why I&#8217;m such a big believer in the &#8220;track every cent that comes in and out of your life&#8221; program central to Your Money or Your Life.  The 20-25% that my wife and I cut were pretty much just the result of being aware of where our money was going each month.  No budgets, no real hardship or sacrifice &#8212; just awareness.</p>
<p>Best of luck in getting the mortgage paid off &#8212; but if you&#8217;re already saving over 50% I&#8217;m sure you&#8217;ll get it done!</p>
</div>

	</div><!-- #comment-##  -->

